3. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with image retrieval. 
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible sub-category as the paper focuses on improving retrieval performance. 
5. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely sub-category as the paper does not explicitly deal with natural language processing, but it does involve mining and processing textual data associated with images.
